HEADWORD: Heterogangliate
<hw>Het`er*o*gan"gli*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + <ets>gangliate</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Having the ganglia of the nervous system
unsymmetrically arranged; -- said of certain invertebrate
animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

